The paper focuses on damage recovery in autonomous robots, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The algorithm proposed in the paper involves machine learning techniques such as self-modeling and learning to avoid certain behaviors, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of sensors and SLAM algorithms to assess the behavior of the robot, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY) and computer vision (cs.CV).
